                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Z-score normalization</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Handles constant columns</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Fit/transform pattern</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Configurable columns</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="transform-card">
                <div class="transform-header">
                    <h3>OneHotEncoder</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="transform-body">
                    <p class="transform-desc">Convert categorical variables into binary columns.</p>
                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Handles NaN values</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Drop first option</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Preserves other columns</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Memory efficient</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="transform-card">
                <div class="transform-header">
                    <h3>LogTransformer</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="transform-body">
                    <p class="transform-desc">Apply logarithmic transformation to numeric columns.</p>
                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> log(1 + x) by default</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Configurable offset</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Handles zero/negative</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Base selection</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="transform-card">
                <div class="transform-header">
                    <h3>MinMaxScaler</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="transform-body">
                    <p class="transform-desc">Scale features to a given range (default 0-1).</p>
                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Custom range support</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Feature-wise scaling</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Robust to outliers</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Preserves shape</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="transform-card">
                <div class="transform-header">
                    <h3>RobustScaler</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="transform-body">
                    <p class="transform-desc">Scale features using statistics robust to outliers.</p>
                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Median/IQR based</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Outlier resistant</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Quantile ranges</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Center option</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="transform-card">
                <div class="transform-header">
                    <h3>ColumnSelector</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="transform-body">
                    <p class="transform-desc">Select specific columns from the dataset.</p>
                    <ul class="transform-features">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Include/exclude lists</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Pattern matching</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Dtype filtering</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check feature-icon"></i> Order preservation</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        <h2>Creating Custom Transforms</h2>
        <div class="usage-example">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-plus-circle"></i> Extending the Pipeline</h3>
            <p>You can create custom transforms by extending the base class:</p>
            <div class="code-example">
from core.transforms import BaseTransform
import pandas as pd

class CustomTransform(BaseTransform):
    def __init__(self, config):
        super().__init__(config)
        self.multiplier = config.get("multiplier", 1)
    
    def fit(self, df: pd.DataFrame):
        # Learn parameters from data
        self.means_ = df.mean()
        return self
    
    def transform(self, df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:
        # Apply transformation
        result = df.copy()
        for col in self.config["columns"]:
            result[col] = (result[col] - self.means_[col]) * self.multiplier
        return result
            
# Register in config:
# transforms:
#   - name: CustomTransform
#     params:
#       columns: ["feature1", "feature2"]
#       multiplier: 2.5
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="navigation">
            <a href="pipeline.html" class="nav-btn prev">
                <i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Previous: Pipeline
            </a>
            <a href="config.html" class="nav-btn">
                Next: Configuration <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
            </a>
        </div>
        
        <footer>
            <p>Duck Brilliance Pipeline Documentation | Transform Reference</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
</body>
</html>
```

5. Create a simple deployment script:

docs/deploy_docs.py

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Deploy documentation to GitHub Pages or other static hosting.
"""

import os
import shutil
import subprocess
from pathlib import Path
import webbrowser

def build_docs():
    """Generate all HTML documentation."""
    print("Building documentation...")
    
    # Run the HTML generator
    subprocess.run([sys.executable, "generate_html.py"], check=True)
    
    # Copy additional assets
    assets_dir = Path("docs/assets")
    assets_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
    
    # Create a simple CSS file
    css_content = """
    /* Additional styles for documentation */
    .method-signature {
        font-family: monospace;
        background: #f5f5f5;
        padding: 10px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin: 10px 0;
    }
    .parameter {
        color: #d35400;
    }
    .return-type {
        color: #27ae60;
    }
    .warning {
        background: #fff3cd;
        border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
        padding: 15px;
        margin: 15px 0;
    }
    """
    
    (assets_dir / "custom.css").write_text(css_content)
    
    print("Documentation built successfully!")

def preview_docs():
    """Preview documentation locally."""
    print("Starting local preview server...")
    print("Open http://localhost:8000 in your browser")
    print("Press Ctrl+C to stop the server")
    
    os.chdir("docs")
    try:
        # Python 3.x simple HTTP server
        import http.server
        import socketserver
        
        PORT = 8000
        Handler = http.server.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler
        
        with socketserver.TCPServer(("", PORT), Handler) as httpd:
            print(f"Serving at http://localhost:{PORT}")
            webbrowser.open(f"http://localhost:{PORT}")
            httpd.serve_forever()
    except KeyboardInterrupt:
        print("\nServer stopped.")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Error: {e}")

def create_sitemap():
    """Create a sitemap for search engines."""
    sitemap = """<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>weekly</changefreq>
        <priority>1.0</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/pipeline.html</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/transforms.html</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/config.html</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/validation.html</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://yourusername.github.io/duck-brilliance-pipeline/cli.html</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-01-01</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
</urlset>"""
    
    (Path("docs") / "sitemap.xml").write_text(sitemap)
    print("Sitemap created!")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    import sys
    
    if len(sys.argv) > 1:
        command = sys.argv[1]
        if command == "build":
            build_docs()
        elif command == "preview":
            preview_docs()
        elif command == "sitemap":
            create_sitemap()
        elif command == "all":
            build_docs()
            create_sitemap()
            preview_docs()
        else:
            print(f"Unknown command: {command}")
            print("Available commands: build, preview, sitemap, all")
    else:
        print("Usage: python deploy_docs.py [command]")
        print("Commands:")
        print("  build    - Generate HTML documentation")
        print("  preview  - Start local preview server")
        print("  sitemap  - Create sitemap.xml")
        print("  all      - Build, create sitemap, and preview")
```

