            <h2>Create Configuration</h2>
            <p>Create a YAML configuration file for your pipeline:</p>
            
            <div class="config-example">
<span class="yaml-key">input_path</span>: <span class="yaml-string">"data/input.csv"</span>
<span class="yaml-key">output_path</span>: <span class="yaml-string">"data/processed.csv"</span>
<span class="yaml-key">progress_bar</span>: <span class="yaml-value">true</span>
<span class="yaml-key">validation_rules</span>:
  - <span class="yaml-string">check_missing</span>
  - <span class="yaml-string">check_duplicates</span>
  - <span class="yaml-string">check_types</span>

<span class="yaml-key">transforms</span>:
  - <span class="yaml-key">name</span>: <span class="yaml-string">StandardScaler</span>
    <span class="yaml-key">params</span>:
      <span class="yaml-key">columns</span>: 
        - <span class="yaml-string">"age"</span>
        - <span class="yaml-string">"income"</span>
        - <span class="yaml-string">"score"</span>
  
  - <span class="yaml-key">name</span>: <span class="yaml-string">OneHotEncoder</span>
    <span class="yaml-key">params</span>:
      <span class="yaml-key">columns</span>: 
        - <span class="yaml-string">"department"</span>
        - <span class="yaml-string">"category"</span>
      <span class="yaml-key">drop_first</span>: <span class="yaml-value">true</span>
            </div>
            
            <p>Save this as <code>pipeline_config.yaml</code> in your project.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <h2>Prepare Your Data</h2>
            <p>Create a sample CSV file to process:</p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
<span class="comment"># data/input.csv</span>
name,age,income,score,department,category
Alice,25,50000,85,Sales,A
Bob,30,60000,92,Engineering,B
Charlie,35,75000,88,Marketing,A
Diana,28,55000,95,Sales,C
Eve,40,80000,90,Engineering,B
            </div>
            
            <div class="file-structure">
<span class="dir">my_project/</span>
├── <span class="file">pipeline_config.yaml</span>
└── <span class="dir">data/</span>
    └── <span class="file">input.csv</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <h2>Run the Pipeline</h2>
            <p>Execute the pipeline using the command line:</p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
<span class="command"># Basic run</span>
duck-brilliance-pipeline -c pipeline_config.yaml

<span class="command"># With verbose output</span>
duck-brilliance-pipeline -c pipeline_config.yaml -vv

<span class="command"># Override input/output paths</span>
duck-brilliance-pipeline -c pipeline_config.yaml \
  -i data/my_data.csv \
  -o results/processed.csv

<span class="command"># Validate only (don't process)</span>
duck-brilliance-pipeline -c pipeline_config.yaml --validate-only
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <h2>Use in Python</h2>
            <p>Integrate the pipeline into your Python code:</p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
<span class="comment"># Import the pipeline</span>
from pipeline.main import DataPipeline

<span class="comment"># Initialize and run</span>
pipeline = DataPipeline("pipeline_config.yaml")
pipeline.initialize()

<span class="comment"># Run the full pipeline</span>
result = pipeline.run()

<span class="comment"># Get execution summary</span>
summary = pipeline.get_summary()
print(f"Processed {summary['input_rows']} rows")
print(f"Applied {summary['transforms_applied']} transforms")

<span class="comment"># Just validate data</span>
data = pipeline.load_data("data/input.csv")
pipeline.validate(data)
print("Validation passed!")

<span class="comment"># Access configuration</span>
config = pipeline.get_config()
print(f"Input: {config['input_path']}")
print(f"Output: {config['output_path']}")
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tips">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Pro Tips</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Start with <code>--validate-only</code> to check your data before processing</li>
                <li>Use <code>-vv</code> flag for detailed debugging output</li>
                <li>Check the <code>data/output.csv</code> after running to see transformations</li>
                <li>Add <code>validate_after_each: true</code> in config to validate after each transform</li>
                <li>Use JSON format if you need programmatic config generation</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
